text: [Music]
hello i'm karthik a cloud support
engineer here at the aws dallas office
today i'm going to show you what you can
do if you get an error
when trying to open a jupyter notebook
on amazon sagemaker notebook instance
in a browser let's get started from the
aws management console open the amazon
sagemaker console
and confirm that the notebook instance
is in service
try to open the jupyter notebook on
amazon sagemaker
notebook instance in a different browser
if you still can't open the jupyter
notebook check jupyter logs for
errors
this issue can also happen when a
notebook instance
is overloaded due to common causes such
as
too many open sessions high cpu
or memory or disk utilization issues
run the top free hyphen h and
df hyphen h commands in a terminal
of the amazon search maker notebook
instance
to check cpu memory and disk utilization
if you still can't open the jupyter
notebook restart the notebook instance
it's a best practice to regularly
restart notebook instances
restarting helps keep notebook instance
software up to date when you restart the
notebook instance
moves to a new underlying host
to restart a notebook instance open the
amazon sagemaker console
in the navigation pane choose notebook
instance
select the circle next to notebook
instance name
choose the actions drop down menu and
then
choose stop wait for the notebook
instance
to reach the stopped status choose the
actions drop down menu
and then choose start
open the notebook instance url
now you know how to troubleshoot
problems with opening jupyter notebooks
in amazon sagemaker notebook instances
thanks for watching and happy cloud
computing from all of us here at aws
